comments.body:
The issue is here in the code:
https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShell/blob/41b316183015ccc2e7b301a3969ea7228684b4ab/src/System.Management.Automation/engine/LanguagePrimitives.cs#L479
Enumerating DataTables is explicitly disabled .
```
#if !CORECLR
            if (typeof(DataTable).IsAssignableFrom(objectType))
            {
                return LanguagePrimitives.DataTableEnumerable;
            }
#endif
```
I don't know why this was done or if there is any reason not to turn it back on (other than it's a breaking change from 6.0). I've marked it for review by the committee.
